Consumer innovativeness is a construct that deals with how receptive consumers are to new products<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Guhathakurta|first=Rahul|date=2016-05-26|title=Understanding the Profile of a 'Consumer Innovator'|url=https://papers.ssrn.com/abstract=2785429|journal=IndraStra Global|language=en|location=Rochester, NY|volume=|pages=|issn=2381-3652|via=SSRN}}</ref>. Consumer innovativeness has been defined as a predisposition or propensity to buy or adopt new products or a preference for new and different experience.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/9781444316568.wiem03009 |title= Consumer Innovativeness|accessdate=2014-10-29 |doi=10.1002/9781444316568.wiem03009 |journal=Wiley International Encyclopedia of Marketing}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Steenkamp |first=Jan-Benedict |last2=Hofstede |first2=Frenkel ter |last3=Wedel |first3=Michel |date= |title=A Cross-National Investigation into the Individual and National Cultural Antecedents of Consumer Innovativeness |jstor=1251945 |journal= Journal of Marketing |publisher= American Marketing Association |volume=63 |issue=2 |pages=55–69 |doi=10.2307/1251945 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Goldsmith |first=Ronald |last2=Hofacker |first2=Charles |date= |title=Measuring consumer innovativeness |url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02726497 |journal= Journal of Academy of Marketing Science |publisher= Springer |volume=19 |issue=3 |pages=209–221 |doi=10.1007/BF02726497 |access-date=7 May 2016}}</ref><ref>Grewal, Rajdeep, Raj Mehta, and Frank R. Kardes. "The role of the social-identity function of attitudes in consumer innovativeness and opinion leadership." Journal of Economic Psychology 21, no. 3 (2000): 233-252.</ref>
