[[Russian Federation]] is a dual-national state with '''over 185 ethnic groups''' designated as nationalities, population of these groups varying enormously, from millions in case of e.g. Russians and Tatars to under ten thousand in the case of Samis and Kets.<ref name="Alvaro">{{cite web |url=https://wcd.coe.int/ViewDoc.jsp?id=846655 |title=Report by Mr. Alvaro Gil-Robles on his Visits to the Russian Federation |publisher=[[Council of Europe]], [[Commissioner for Human Rights]] |date=2005-04-20 |accessdate=2008-03-16 }}</ref> <!--paragraph 180--> Among [[Federal subjects of Russia|85 subjects]] which constitute the [[Russian Federation]], there are 21 national republics (meant to be home to a specific ethnic minority), 5 autonomous okrugs (usually with substantial or predominant ethnic minority) and an [[Jewish Autonomous Oblast|autonomous oblast]].
