{{confused|Mohmand}}
The '''Mamund'''  (or '''Mamond''') ({{lang-ur|{{nq|مَاموند}}}}, {{lang-ps|{{nq|ماموند}}}}) is a [[Pashtun people|Pashtun]] clan which is a part of the larger [[Tarkani]] tribe. The clan is located principally in the [[Watelai]] valley (also known as Mamund Valley), but also owns villages on both sides of the [[Durand Line]]. Majority of the  Mamund Pashtuns live in [[Bajaur Agency]], one of the seven tribal regions of [[Khyber Pukhtunkhwa]], [[Pakistan]], and in Marawara, Asadabad, Shigal, Watapur and Ghazi Abad Districts of [[Kunar Province|Kunar]] Province in Afghanistan.<ref name="latifyaad">[http://www.khyber.org/books/latifyada.pdf پښتانه قبيلی وپېژنئ - ډاکټر لطيف ياد - خېبر وېب پاڼه] - pp 86-89 & 261-262 & 310-312 (in Pashto)</ref>{{qn|date=December 2017}}

The Mamund clan is split into two divisions: [[Kakazai]] and [[Wur|Wara]].<ref name="latifyaad"/>{{qn|date=December 2017}}

